HEADWORD: Matronly
<hw>Ma"tron*ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Advanced in years;
elderly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Like, or befitting, a matron; grave;
sedate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Matronymic</ent>⟦br⟧
